{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HaJKsv5YrKWXVV5tMae9v1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's a summary of all changes made:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### AC 3 Fix: Gap data now flows through the gate pipeline\n\n**Root cause:** `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` hardcoded `gapSummary = []` and never read cached gap data.\n\n**Files modified:**\n\n1. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/coverage.ts` (299 lines)\n   - `saveCoverageResult()` now persists `result.gaps` into `observability.static.gaps` in sprint-state.json, so gap data is cached for the gate to read.\n\n2. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/coverage-gate.ts` (121 lines)\n   - Added `readCachedGaps()` function that reads `observability.static.gaps` from sprint-state.json with defensive type validation.\n   - `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` now calls `readCachedGaps()` instead of returning an empty array.\n\n3. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/observability-gate.ts` (114 lines)\n   - Text output now shows gap details (top 5 with `file:line — description` format) when gate fails.\n   - Removed reference to nonexistent `codeharness analyze` command. Now says \"Add logging to flagged functions. See: patches/observability/ for rule definitions.\"\n\n4. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/hooks/pre-commit-gate.sh` (114 lines)\n   - Changed \"codeharness analyze\" references to \"codeharness observability-gate\".\n   - Updated block message to reference `patches/observability/` for rule definitions.\n\n5. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/__tests__/coverage-gate.test.ts`\n   - Updated gap test: now tests that cached gaps from sprint-state.json are returned.\n   - Added test for malformed gap entries (graceful degradation).\n   - Added test that verifies gap data with file/line/description/severity fields.\n\n6. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/observability-gate.test.ts`\n   - Updated fail message assertion from \"codeharness analyze\" to \"Add logging to flagged functions\".\n   - Added test verifying gap details appear in text output.\n\n7. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-2-observability-hook-enforcement.md`\n   - Status changed from \"verifying\" to \"review\".\n\n**Verification:** Build succeeds, 2625 tests pass, all files under 300-line NFR9 limit.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **`coverage-gate.ts` reads sprint-state.json twice:** Once via `readCoverageState()` (for coverage numbers) and once via `readCachedGaps()` (for gap data). This is because `ObservabilityCoverageState` type doesn't include a `gaps` field, and adding it would cascade through many consumers. Acceptable for now since the file is small and cached by the OS, but should be consolidated if performance matters.\n- **No `codeharness analyze` command exists:** The story references it in multiple places but it was never implemented. Changed all references to point to `codeharness observability-gate` or `patches/observability/` instead. A proper `analyze` CLI command should be created in a future story.\n- **Gaps only populate after `saveCoverageResult` is called:** If sprint-state.json was written by an older version without the `gaps` field, the gate will return empty gaps. This is correct behavior (graceful degradation) but means AC 3 only fully works after at least one analyzer run."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a04efb2f5b8c2c8f7 (use SendMessage with to: 'a04efb2f5b8c2c8f7' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 67631\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 230146</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fa32674-558d-4231-8eb7-1997dc535a41","uuid":"3819305b-d238-40d6-8195-61f2121a643c","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:19:17.810Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-2-observability-hook-enforcement.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nIMPORTANT — VERIFICATION FINDINGS FROM PREVIOUS CYCLE:\nThe following ACs failed verification. Fix the code to make them pass:\n\n## Verification Findings\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-20T06:10Z_\n\nThe following ACs failed black-box verification:\n\n### AC 3: Given hook blocks, When the message is displayed, Then it includes specific files/functions missing logging and how to fix\n**Verdict:** FAIL\n**Error output:**\n```\n{\"status\":\"fail\",\"passed\":false,\"static\":{\"current\":72,\"target\":80,\"met\":false,\"gap\":8},\"runtime\":null,\"gaps\":[]}\n```\n\nRoot cause: `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` in `coverage-gate.ts` hardcodes `gapSummary = []` — it never reads gap data from `sprint-state.json` nor calls any analyzer function. The output formatting code correctly maps `gate.gapSummary` to the `gaps` JSON field, but since the source array is always empty, no gaps are ever displayed.\n\nAdditionally, the block message references `codeharness analyze` but no such CLI command exists.\n\n**What must be fixed:**\n1. `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` must read gap data from sprint-state.json (the `observability.static.gaps` array if it exists) or call the analyzer to get current gaps\n2. The `observability-gate` command must include gap details in both human-readable and JSON output\n3. Either create a `codeharness analyze` subcommand or change the message to reference an existing command\n\nRead the findings carefully. Each failing AC includes the error output from the verifier. Your job is to fix the underlying code so these ACs pass on the next verification run. Do NOT remove the ## Verification Findings section from the story file — it stays for reference.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a04efb2f5b8c2c8f7","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's a summary of all changes made:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### AC 3 Fix: Gap data now flows through the gate pipeline\n\n**Root cause:** `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` hardcoded `gapSummary = []` and never read cached gap data.\n\n**Files modified:**\n\n1. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/coverage.ts` (299 lines)\n   - `saveCoverageResult()` now persists `result.gaps` into `observability.static.gaps` in sprint-state.json, so gap data is cached for the gate to read.\n\n2. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/coverage-gate.ts` (121 lines)\n   - Added `readCachedGaps()` function that reads `observability.static.gaps` from sprint-state.json with defensive type validation.\n   - `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` now calls `readCachedGaps()` instead of returning an empty array.\n\n3. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/observability-gate.ts` (114 lines)\n   - Text output now shows gap details (top 5 with `file:line — description` format) when gate fails.\n   - Removed reference to nonexistent `codeharness analyze` command. Now says \"Add logging to flagged functions. See: patches/observability/ for rule definitions.\"\n\n4. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/hooks/pre-commit-gate.sh` (114 lines)\n   - Changed \"codeharness analyze\" references to \"codeharness observability-gate\".\n   - Updated block message to reference `patches/observability/` for rule definitions.\n\n5. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/__tests__/coverage-gate.test.ts`\n   - Updated gap test: now tests that cached gaps from sprint-state.json are returned.\n   - Added test for malformed gap entries (graceful degradation).\n   - Added test that verifies gap data with file/line/description/severity fields.\n\n6. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/observability-gate.test.ts`\n   - Updated fail message assertion from \"codeharness analyze\" to \"Add logging to flagged functions\".\n   - Added test verifying gap details appear in text output.\n\n7. `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-2-observability-hook-enforcement.md`\n   - Status changed from \"verifying\" to \"review\".\n\n**Verification:** Build succeeds, 2625 tests pass, all files under 300-line NFR9 limit.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **`coverage-gate.ts` reads sprint-state.json twice:** Once via `readCoverageState()` (for coverage numbers) and once via `readCachedGaps()` (for gap data). This is because `ObservabilityCoverageState` type doesn't include a `gaps` field, and adding it would cascade through many consumers. Acceptable for now since the file is small and cached by the OS, but should be consolidated if performance matters.\n- **No `codeharness analyze` command exists:** The story references it in multiple places but it was never implemented. Changed all references to point to `codeharness observability-gate` or `patches/observability/` instead. A proper `analyze` CLI command should be created in a future story.\n- **Gaps only populate after `saveCoverageResult` is called:** If sprint-state.json was written by an older version without the `gaps` field, the gate will return empty gaps. This is correct behavior (graceful degradation) but means AC 3 only fully works after at least one analyzer run."}],"totalDurationMs":230146,"totalTokens":67631,"totalToolUseCount":38,"