{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013UmTg4yvWHTnhcG8r3ZDFJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019hCrLufVfh7eo7iMbpMuDU","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","old_string":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 2)","new_string":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 3)\n\n### 2-2-observability-hook-enforcement — dev-story AC3 fix (2026-03-20T06:18Z)\n\n- **`coverage-gate.ts` reads sprint-state.json twice:** Once via `readCoverageState()` for coverage numbers and once via `readCachedGaps()` for gap data. `ObservabilityCoverageState` type doesn't include gaps field — adding it would cascade. Acceptable for now.\n- **No `codeharness analyze` command exists:** Changed all references to point to `codeharness observability-gate` or `patches/observability/` instead.\n- **Gaps only populate after `saveCoverageResult` is called:** If sprint-state.json was written by older version without gaps field, gate returns empty gaps. Graceful degradation but means AC 3 only fully works after at least one analyzer run.\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 2)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2937,"cache_read_input_tokens":47905,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2937},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fa32674-558d-4231-8eb7-1997dc535a41","uuid":"69483ec8-1370-476b-9557-70e4298633c2"}
