   375→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   376→      \"resolved\": false\n   377→    },\n   378→    {\n   379→      \"id\": \"migrated-24\",\n   380→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   381→      \"description\": \"**Import boundary violation (fixed):** `runtime-coverage.ts` initially imported from `../verify/types.js` directly. Fixed to use barrel import.\",\n   382→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   383→      \"resolved\": false\n   384→    },\n   385→    {\n   386→      \"id\": \"migrated-25\",\n   387→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   388→      \"description\": \"**logEventCount is binary:** Set to 0 or 1 based on gap presence, not actual log event count. Parser only detects `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag presence.\",\n   389→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   390→      \"resolved\": false\n   391→    },\n   392→    {\n   393→      \"id\": \"migrated-26\",\n   394→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   395→      \"description\": \"**VerifyResult field additions are breaking:** All existing `VerifyResult` constructions needed updating (5 files). Optional fields with defaults would reduce churn.\",\n   396→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   397→      \"resolved\": false\n   398→    },\n   399→    {\n   400→      \"id\": \"migrated-27\",\n   401→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   402→      \"description\": \"**Task 2.4 no-op:** No new config fields needed — existing `observabilityEndpoints.victoriaLogs` already sufficient.\",\n   403→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   404→      \"resolved\": false\n   405→    },\n   406→    {\n   407→      \"id\": \"migrated-28\",\n   408→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   409→      \"description\": \"**HIGH: saveRuntimeCoverage was dead code** — never called from production, only tested. Runtime coverage would never persist to sprint-state.json. Fixed.\",\n   410→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   411→      \"resolved\": false\n   412→    },\n   413→    {\n   414→      \"id\": \"migrated-29\",\n   415→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   416→      \"description\": \"**MEDIUM: verify.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — command always reported 0 observability gaps regardless of proof content. Fixed.\",\n   417→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   418→      \"resolved\": false\n   419→    },\n   420→    {\n   421→      \"id\": \"migrated-30\",\n   422→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   423→      \"description\": \"**MEDIUM: verifier-session.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — same pattern as verify.ts. Fixed.\",\n   424→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   425→      \"resolved\": false\n   426→    },\n   427→    {\n   428→      \"id\": \"migrated-31\",\n   429→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   430→      \"description\": \"**LOW (not fixed): Binary logEventCount** — always 0 or 1, not actual log counts. Tech debt.\",\n   431→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   432→      \"resolved\": false\n   433→    },\n   434→    {\n   435→      \"id\": \"migrated-32\",\n   436→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   437→      \"description\": \"**LOW (not fixed): Duplicated coverage math** — verify/index.ts duplicates computeRuntimeCoverage logic.\",\n   438→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   439→      \"resolved\": false\n   440→    },\n   441→    {\n   442→      \"id\": \"migrated-33\",\n   443→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   444→      \"description\": \"**LOW (not fixed): Silent catch blocks** — gap parsing errors silently swallowed in 3 locations.\",\n   445→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   446→      \"resolved\": false\n   447→    },\n   448→    {\n   449→      \"id\": \"migrated-34\",\n   450→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   451→      \"description\": \"**Architecture: Hardcoded CWD** — verifyStory() calls saveRuntimeCoverage with '.' as projectDir, assumes CWD is project root.\",\n   452→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   453→      \"resolved\": false\n   454→    },\n   455→    {\n   456→      \"id\": \"migrated-35\",\n   457→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   458→      \"description\": \"**Architecture: Triple gap parsing** — 3 separate locations independently parse gaps. Should be centralized.\",\n   459→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   460→      \"resolved\": false\n   461→    },\n   462→    {\n   463→      \"id\": \"migrated-36\",\n   464→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   465→      \"description\": \"**Proof markdown parsing bug:** Verifier embedded a heredoc containing nested code fences (````bash`/````output`) inside a bash code block. The closing backticks broke out of the outer fence, causing `## AC N: PASS` headings from the test proof to appear as real AC sections. The proof parser counted 8 ACs instead of 4. Fixed by summarizing the heredoc content.\",\n   466→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   467→      \"resolved\": false\n   468→    },\n   469→    {\n   470→      \"id\": \"migrated-37\",\n   471→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   472→      \"description\": \"**Evidence adjacency requirement:** The proof parser requires `bash` and `output` code blocks to be adjacent (no text between them). AC3 had explanatory text between the blocks, causing it to be counted as pending. Fixed by removing the intervening text.\",\n   473→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   474→      \"resolved\": false\n   475→    },\n   476→    {\n   477→      \"id\": \"migrated-38\",\n   478→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   479→      \"description\": \"**VictoriaLogs zero events:** The codeharness CLI does not emit OpenTelemetry data in the Docker container, so all observability gap checks return empty. This is expected for a tool that instruments other projects, not itself.\",\n   480→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   481→      \"resolved\": false\n   482→    },\n   483→    {\n   484→      \"id\": \"migrated-39\",\n   485→      \"story\": \"2-1-verification-observability-check\",\n   486→      \"description\": \"**AC1 template verification limitation:** The verify-prompt.ts template compiles into the Claude Code plugin (skills/), not the npm CLI binary. Cannot directly inspect the template from Docker. Verified via the template-to-parser contract (OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG constant, parseObservabilityGaps function, verify --json output fields).\",\n   487→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   488→      \"resolved\": false\n   489→    }\n   490→  ]\n   491→}\n   492→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KDp23Ghg12YdfCMhs2iDP9","session_id":"2fa32674-558d-4231-8eb7-1997dc535a41","uuid":"45fabe0f-7287-4bbb-bf92-04b8d7c4f693","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:20:11.737Z"}
