{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KDp23Ghg12YdfCMhs2iDP9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the summary of what was done and the session issues.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nPerformed adversarial code review of Story 2.2 (Observability Hook Enforcement). Found and fixed 3 issues (2 HIGH, 1 MEDIUM):\n\n### Fixes Applied\n\n1. **HIGH: Double file read in `coverage-gate.ts`** — `checkObservabilityCoverageGate()` called `readCoverageState()` (which reads sprint-state.json), then `readCachedGaps()` read the same file again independently. This was wasteful and could produce incoherent results if the file changed between reads. Fixed by adding `gaps` to the `StaticCoverageState` type, parsing gaps in `extractCoverageState()` within `coverage.ts`, and reading them from the already-parsed state in `coverage-gate.ts`. Removed unused `readFileSync`/`existsSync`/`join` imports from `coverage-gate.ts`.\n\n2. **HIGH: Gaps not surfaced through `readCoverageState`** — `saveCoverageResult()` persisted gaps to `sprint-state.json` under `observability.static.gaps`, but `extractCoverageState()` never parsed them back, and `StaticCoverageState` had no `gaps` field. This was the root cause of AC 3's failure (gaps always empty). Fixed by adding `gaps?: readonly ObservabilityGap[]` to `StaticCoverageState` and adding `parseGapArray()` helper to `coverage.ts`.\n\n3. **MEDIUM: Fix suggestion references nonexistent command** — `observability-gate.ts` text output said \"See: patches/observability/ for rule definitions\" which is unhelpful. Changed to \"Run: codeharness observability-gate for details\" which references the actual working command.\n\n### Files Modified\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/types.ts` — added `gaps` field to `StaticCoverageState`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/coverage.ts` — added `parseGapArray()`, gap parsing in `extractCoverageState()`, added imports for `ObservabilityGap`/`GapSeverity`. Compressed docstrings to stay under 300 lines (now 290).\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/observability/coverage-gate.ts` — removed independent file read, now uses gaps from `readCoverageState()`. Removed unused `node:fs`/`node:path` imports. File reduced from 121 to 80 lines.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/observability-gate.ts` — updated fix suggestion text\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/observability-gate.test.ts` — updated assertion to match new text\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-2-observability-hook-enforcement.md` — status changed to `verifying`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/sprint-state.json` — story status changed to `verifying`\n\n### Results\n- Build: passes\n- Tests: 2625/2625 pass (101 test files)\n- Coverage: 96.42% overall, all 109 files above 80% per-file floor\n- All NFR9 file size limits met (coverage.ts: 290/300, coverage-gate.ts: 80/300)\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed (HIGH/MEDIUM):**\n- HIGH: `coverage-gate.ts` double-read of sprint-state.json — inconsistent reads, wasted I/O. Fixed.\n- HIGH: Gaps never parsed back from sprint-state.json through `readCoverageState` — `StaticCoverageState` type lacked `gaps` field, so AC 3 (gap details in block message) always showed empty. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Fix suggestion in `observability-gate.ts` referenced generic \"patches/observability/\" path instead of an actionable command. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority, tech debt):**\n- LOW: Grep-based JSON parsing in `pre-commit-gate.sh` is fragile — works for current output shapes but could break with nested JSON or different formatting. Pre-existing pattern used for all hook checks; not specific to this story.\n- LOW: `DEFAULT_STATIC_TARGET` and `DEFAULT_RUNTIME_TARGET` constants duplicated in both `coverage.ts` and `coverage-gate.ts` — should be a single shared constant.\n- LOW: `coverage-gate.ts` still has `import { ok, fail }` from result.ts but `fail` is the Result `fail` constructor, not the output `fail` — naming collision risk with `observability-gate.ts` which imports both. Not a bug, but confusing.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `index.ts` barrel files show 0% coverage (type-only re-exports, no executable code — expected).\n- `types.ts` files show 0% coverage (interface-only files — expected).\n- No integration test for the full end-to-end flow: write state with gaps -> run `observability-gate --json` -> verify gaps appear in output. Unit tests mock at module boundaries, so the gap-parsing integration path between `coverage.ts` and `coverage-gate.ts` is only tested through the unit test mocks.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The hook (`pre-commit-gate.sh`) can only display gap details if `saveCoverageResult` was previously run to persist them. If the user has never run an analysis, the hook blocks on coverage but can't show gap details — acceptable per story design, but worth documenting.\n- `parseGapArray()` in `coverage.ts` duplicates validation logic that also exists in the `saveCoverageResult` path — the gap objects are validated on write and re-validated on read. Defensive but redundant.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story moved to `verifying`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0d6677b7fbe64be8 (use SendMessage with to: 'a0d6677b7fbe64be8' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 73208\ntool_uses: 54\nduration_ms: 311854</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2fa32674-558d-4231-8eb7-1997dc535a41","uuid":"75c57876-892c-4c36-b70f-5f6206e4cf88","timestamp":"2026-03-20T06:25:05.649Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-2-observability-hook-enforcement.md — perform adversarial review, fix 